result.execSummary:
The defendant was charged with both OWI (4th) and Operating w/ PAC (4th). The defendant was found guilty of OWI (4th) and the other charge, Operating w/ PAC (4th) was dismissed by the court.

  • Jack T Melaney was found guilty of Vehicle Operator Flee/Elude Officer, a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 346.04(3).
  • Jack T Melaney was found guilty of OWI (4th), an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 346.63(1)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
2:13 p.m.  Defendant present in court with Atty Barb Privat.  Andrew Christenson for the State of Wisconsin.  Court reads the plea offer - defendant will plea to count 1 & 2, and counts 3 & 4 will be dismissed.  Atty Privat concurs.  Defendant concurs.

Court goes over plea questionnaire with the defendant.  Court goes over constitutional rights with the defendant - defendant waives these rights.  Court goes over the elements of each offense.  Court instructs defendant of the maximum penalty.  Court instructs defendant regarding deportation.  (If felony) Court instructs regarding felony prohibitions.  Defendant enters a plea of GUILTY to counts 1 & 2.  Court finds the plea is made freely, voluntarily, intelligently and understandingly.  Court finds there is a factual basis to support the plea.  Court finds the defendant guilty to counts 1 & 2.  Court orders counts 3 & 4 be dismissed.  Court orders the judgment of conviction be entered here today.  Sentencing statement by DA.  Argument by Atty Privat.  Statement by the defendant.

Court sentences the defendant to:

COUNT 1 - SWD, and places the defendant on probation for 36 months.

CONDITIONS:
-AODA 
-D.L. revocation for 6 months
-Court costs
-other conditions as imposed by the supervising agent

COUNT 2 - 

-OWI Assessment
-D.L. Revocation - 30 months
-IID - 30 months
-Blood Draw fee - $28.50
-$1200 fine plus costs - $2252.00 (IID included)
-70 days jail, with huber

Court remands the defendant to the custody of the Green Lake County Jail.

Court grants the defendant 60 days to pay or payment plan.  Statement by the Court in regards to sentence credit - grants the defendant credit for the time spent in custody and the jail knows that amount.  

Court adjourned at 2:30 p.m.
